WEBVTT

00:02.166 --> 00:04.000
[bright tone]

00:04.791 --> 00:07.750
<i>[light dramatic music]</i>

00:07.833 --> 00:11.083
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:11.166 --> 00:14.375
[cell phone buzzing]

00:18.625 --> 00:19.916
<i>- Hello?</i>

00:20.000 --> 00:23.708
- Hey, Lylah, it's Richard.
Your brother.

00:23.791 --> 00:28.166
<i>- Richard, I...haven't heard</i>
<i>your voice in years.</i>

00:29.833 --> 00:31.208
- [sighs]

00:31.291 --> 00:32.583
Listen, I need your help.

00:32.666 --> 00:34.125
- I'm listening.

00:34.208 --> 00:39.708
- Well, wouldn't you know,
the boy is making waves.

00:39.791 --> 00:41.250
<i>[sighs]</i>

00:41.333 --> 00:42.708
You know, it seems that
he's hiding out

00:42.791 --> 00:44.208
in your house in Massachusetts.

00:44.291 --> 00:46.625
- Oh, that's fine.
I always hated that house.

00:46.708 --> 00:49.166
- And we believe that he, uh--

00:49.250 --> 00:54.625
I hate using this word--
uh, kidnapped a woman.

00:54.708 --> 00:55.750
- Oh.

00:55.833 --> 00:57.416
- I'm calling so that we can

00:57.500 --> 00:59.791
just keep this in the family.

01:01.208 --> 01:04.541
You have to do whatever it
takes to just keep this quiet.

01:04.625 --> 01:07.333
- Well, that's what I do,
Richard.

01:07.416 --> 01:09.541
I keep things quiet.

01:09.625 --> 01:11.291
- Great.
That was it.

01:11.375 --> 01:12.750
Listen, if you need anything,

01:12.833 --> 01:15.416
just put it on
the company card, okay?

01:15.500 --> 01:17.375
- Okay.

01:17.458 --> 01:19.583
I see how it is.

01:19.666 --> 01:23.208
"Hello, Lylah.
Just put it on the card.

01:23.291 --> 01:26.333
Just put it on the card, Lylah.
Just put it on the card."

01:26.416 --> 01:28.125
Well, I have my own cards,
you know.

01:28.208 --> 01:29.541
<i>- Okay. Fine.</i>

01:29.625 --> 01:31.666
<i>I'm sorry.</i>
<i>Didn't mean to ruffle you.</i>

01:31.750 --> 01:33.583
I thought we put
the past behind us.

01:33.666 --> 01:37.083
- And yet, here we are.

01:37.166 --> 01:38.208
- [sighs]

01:38.291 --> 01:40.583
<i>- Fine, I'll take care of it.</i>

01:40.666 --> 01:44.166
And Richard...

01:44.250 --> 01:46.625
it's lovely hearing from you.

01:46.708 --> 01:49.000
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:49.083 --> 01:50.541
I miss you.

01:50.625 --> 01:52.416
<i>- I miss you too.</i>

01:52.500 --> 01:54.833
<i>Hey, Lylah?</i>
- Yes?

01:55.458 --> 01:58.208
- Thank you.
<i>- Anytime.</i>

02:04.666 --> 02:06.833
Nadia!

02:08.125 --> 02:09.791
<i>- Da?</i>
- Prepare the plane.

02:09.875 --> 02:13.250
- Where to, Ms. Lylah?
- Babyfoot.

02:13.333 --> 02:15.875
<i>[electronic music]</i>

02:15.958 --> 02:21.458
<i>- ♪ Oh, but dear,</i>
<i>the sky is low watch ♪</i>

02:21.541 --> 02:23.541
<i>♪ Fluent sea men rig ♪</i>

02:23.625 --> 02:24.583
- I don't wanna do this.

02:24.666 --> 02:26.541
I do not wanna do this, okay?

02:26.625 --> 02:27.500
If I call Marc

02:27.583 --> 02:28.666
and ask him where Dory is,

02:28.750 --> 02:30.000
he's gonna think I'm, like,

02:30.083 --> 02:31.208
begging him to take me back,

02:31.291 --> 02:32.791
and then he'll think
that he won.

02:32.875 --> 02:33.833
- Yeah, I mean, no offense,

02:33.916 --> 02:36.291
but he did win.

02:36.375 --> 02:37.916
I mean, he left you
at the altar.

02:38.000 --> 02:39.708
That's, like,
a huge win for him.

02:39.791 --> 02:41.041
- Yeah, babe.

02:41.125 --> 02:42.958
There is no coming back
from that, sorry.

02:43.041 --> 02:45.500
- I have a TV show! I won!

02:45.583 --> 02:48.291
- Oh, you sold your soul
to the devil for that show.

02:48.375 --> 02:50.333
He won!
- Oh, fuck you guys!

02:50.416 --> 02:51.583
Like I would ever take

02:51.666 --> 02:53.041
relationship advice from
you virgins!

02:53.125 --> 02:54.416
- [gasps]
- Excuse you?

02:54.500 --> 02:55.916
- Give me the phone.
- I'm not a virgin.

02:56.000 --> 02:57.916
I lost my virginity young.

02:58.000 --> 02:59.875
- Let's get this over with.

03:01.333 --> 03:04.541
[cell phone buzzing]

03:06.375 --> 03:07.750
- Oh, my God.

03:07.833 --> 03:11.583
Let it ring once.
Let it ring twice.

03:11.666 --> 03:12.625
Hello?

03:12.708 --> 03:14.916
- Hey, can I speak to Marc?

03:15.000 --> 03:16.875
<i>- This is he.</i>

03:16.958 --> 03:18.208
Is this Elliott?

03:18.291 --> 03:21.166
- Yeah, hey, it's Elliott!

03:22.125 --> 03:23.583
[birds chirping]

03:23.666 --> 03:26.083
What's up?

03:26.166 --> 03:27.416
Not much.

03:27.500 --> 03:29.041
Just bought a crib.

03:29.125 --> 03:30.625
<i>I'm trying to adopt a baby,</i>

03:30.708 --> 03:33.208
<i>but it's a lot harder</i>
<i>than you'd think.</i>

03:33.291 --> 03:34.875
- Whoa, a baby?

03:34.958 --> 03:36.625
<i>- Yeah, you know,</i>

03:36.708 --> 03:38.750
I'm just ready to be a dad.

03:38.833 --> 03:41.666
<i>Though I made the mistake on</i>
<i>my application of checking off</i>

03:41.750 --> 03:44.250
<i>the "Do you use drugs</i>
<i>recreationally?"</i>

03:44.333 --> 03:46.750
And then in the margin,
I just wrote "coke."

03:46.833 --> 03:48.208
Sorry.

03:48.291 --> 03:50.625
I think it hurt my odds.
I'm so sorry, ma'am.

03:50.708 --> 03:53.125
- Totally.
That's insane.

03:53.208 --> 03:54.625
Do you know where Dory is?

03:54.708 --> 03:58.291
- Oh, okay.
I see what this is about.

03:58.375 --> 04:00.291
Someone is jealous

04:00.375 --> 04:03.125
that I organically infiltrated
their friend group.

04:03.208 --> 04:05.041
<i>Well, Dory and I don't</i>
<i>need your permission</i>

04:05.125 --> 04:06.541
<i>to hang out, okay?</i>

04:06.625 --> 04:10.375
It is what it is.
You need to let go of the past.

04:10.458 --> 04:13.791
- Oh--are you--is this about
the whole wedding thing?

04:13.875 --> 04:17.416
Okay, come on.
Marc, we were kids, okay?

04:17.500 --> 04:19.250
And I'm sincerely having
trouble remembering

04:19.333 --> 04:21.500
who left who at the altar.

04:21.583 --> 04:23.208
No, no.

04:23.291 --> 04:24.833
I'm just kind of
worried about Dory.

04:24.916 --> 04:27.333
She's been
kind of MIA recently,

04:27.416 --> 04:30.708
and I just wanted to know
where you saw her.

04:30.791 --> 04:32.500
- Oh, I wouldn't
worry about her.

04:32.583 --> 04:34.833
I saw her in this
delicious ice cream shop

04:34.916 --> 04:38.583
in this little town in
Massachusetts called Babyfoot.

04:38.666 --> 04:40.416
<i>It's adorable.</i>
- [mouthing words]

04:40.500 --> 04:43.333
<i>It's shaped like</i>
<i>a baby's foot.</i>

04:43.416 --> 04:45.208
- [mouthing words]

04:45.291 --> 04:46.666
- [laughs]

04:46.750 --> 04:49.333
Did she seem like she was
in any danger or anything?

04:49.416 --> 04:50.958
- No, not at all.

04:51.041 --> 04:53.916
She looked really happy.
Great wig.

04:54.000 --> 04:56.958
<i>And we had a really</i>
<i>incredible conversation.</i>

04:57.041 --> 04:59.875
She did scream, "Dory is dead"
and then run away from me,

04:59.958 --> 05:02.041
but, you know,
I think that was my fault.

05:02.125 --> 05:03.833
<i>I'm so weird socially--</i>
[phone cuts off]

05:03.916 --> 05:06.458
- We're going to Babyfoot.

05:06.541 --> 05:09.541
[footsteps approaching]

05:09.625 --> 05:11.875
- Oh, my goodness.

05:11.958 --> 05:13.041
Call baby brother.

05:13.125 --> 05:14.208
<i>[line trilling]</i>

05:14.291 --> 05:15.708
<i>- Hello?</i>
- Richard.

05:15.791 --> 05:18.250
I made it to Babyfoot,
and I'm in the house.

05:18.333 --> 05:20.541
Chip is not.

05:20.625 --> 05:23.000
The situation
has turned sour, though.

05:23.083 --> 05:25.583
There's a dead body.
<i>- Oh, the Dory girl?</i>

05:25.666 --> 05:28.083
Oh, uh...

05:29.541 --> 05:33.583
No, I don't think
it is the Dory girl.

05:33.666 --> 05:38.291
This woman is old.
Provincial.

05:39.333 --> 05:43.708
Oh, and there's a room
full of chains.

05:43.791 --> 05:46.833
I don't remember them being
there when we bought the house.

05:46.916 --> 05:49.375
<i>- Huh.</i>
<i>Wow.</i>

05:51.125 --> 05:56.541
- Well, it looks like someone
<i>has </i>been living here.

06:00.625 --> 06:03.125
Oh, so creative.

06:03.208 --> 06:07.583
Oh, he could have been
such a successful artist.

06:07.666 --> 06:10.000
Well, there it is.

06:10.083 --> 06:13.333
Torture, captivity,
murder most foul.

06:13.416 --> 06:14.708
That is what they're gonna say.

06:14.791 --> 06:16.291
And who knows
what really happened?

06:16.375 --> 06:17.958
He's such a sweet boy.
<i>- [indistinct]</i>

06:18.041 --> 06:20.791
- No, don't worry.
I'll take care of everything.

06:20.875 --> 06:22.791
Damage control.

06:22.875 --> 06:25.791
- Hi, sweetheart.
I have a question.

06:25.875 --> 06:28.875
There used to be a candy bar
with a big hole in it.

06:28.958 --> 06:31.625
It was long and thin
but thick enough

06:31.708 --> 06:33.791
for there to be
a stable hole in it.

06:33.875 --> 06:35.916
Do you remember
what I'm talking about?

06:36.000 --> 06:37.500
I've been on the hunt for it
for years.

06:37.583 --> 06:39.625
- Well, I don't know.
We got muffins.

06:39.708 --> 06:41.583
We--yeah, I don't know.
I'm not sure.

06:41.666 --> 06:45.458
Is there anywhere,
maybe back there, that you--

06:45.541 --> 06:48.291
- ...and I'll just
track her down

06:48.375 --> 06:49.958
and we'll pay her off.

06:50.041 --> 06:52.041
Unless, of course,
she's just thankful,

06:52.125 --> 06:53.916
grateful for such
a wonderful experience,

06:54.000 --> 06:55.791
and then maybe
she won't want anything.

06:55.875 --> 06:58.375
Well, $50,000, $60,000.
I don't know.

06:58.458 --> 07:00.666
I mean, I don't know
what kind of person she is.

07:00.750 --> 07:02.916
Hi.
I want gas.

07:03.000 --> 07:04.541
I want all the gas
that you have.

07:04.625 --> 07:07.458
That's my car right out in
front, just put it in there.

07:08.666 --> 07:09.833
[bell rings]

07:09.916 --> 07:11.500
- This is $1,000.

07:11.583 --> 07:13.166
- It is, isn't it?

07:13.250 --> 07:15.166
That's for all the gas
you have.

07:15.250 --> 07:19.000
And this is another $1,000

07:19.083 --> 07:21.833
so that you don't tell anybody
about this.

07:21.916 --> 07:24.000
- We're talking $2,000 now.

07:24.083 --> 07:27.041
- Yes.
One and one is $2,000.

07:28.041 --> 07:32.791
And this is my friend.
She's missing.

07:32.875 --> 07:35.333
And I thought maybe
you'd seen her around town.

07:35.416 --> 07:37.791
You know, we're very
concerned about her.

07:37.875 --> 07:40.500
[air hissing]

07:44.083 --> 07:45.791
[object clangs]

07:46.833 --> 07:49.583
- We got one hour.
- What for?

07:49.666 --> 07:51.958
To pack up our entire lives
and start over.

07:52.041 --> 07:53.541
- Why?
What's happening?

07:53.625 --> 07:56.291
- My family is in town!
- Oh.

07:56.375 --> 07:59.541
[engine revs]

08:02.375 --> 08:04.875
[tires squeal]

08:10.250 --> 08:12.625
- All right, we're here.
- Oh, boy.

08:12.708 --> 08:15.625
Okay, I'm only just now seeing
some of these comments.

08:15.708 --> 08:17.208
"Something's off about her."

08:17.291 --> 08:18.875
"Prayers for her."
"Wow."

08:18.958 --> 08:21.000
"Am I the only one
who finds her very strange?"

08:21.083 --> 08:24.541
"Fester Addams with a wig."

08:24.625 --> 08:26.125
That's mean.
- Yeah.

08:26.208 --> 08:28.166
- And she's our friend, so...

08:28.250 --> 08:30.833
- All right. Everybody ready?
- Yeah.

08:30.916 --> 08:33.958
- Portia, what on Earth
are you doing?

08:34.041 --> 08:35.416
- Ugh, Drew.

08:35.500 --> 08:37.458
I'm doing promotional stuff
for my movie, okay?

08:37.541 --> 08:39.666
They're, like, making me post
this official announcement

08:39.750 --> 08:41.583
of myself playing Dory
on my social media.

08:41.666 --> 08:43.250
Anyway, it's just, like,

08:43.333 --> 08:45.583
showbiz stuff you wouldn't
understand, Drew--no offense.

08:45.666 --> 08:48.000
Okay, don't talk. [laughs]
Okay, thank you.

08:48.083 --> 08:49.666
Hi, everybody!

08:49.750 --> 08:52.458
I'm so excited to share with
you an exclusive first look,

08:52.541 --> 08:55.708
sneak peek of my transformation
as Dory Sief

08:55.791 --> 08:57.375
in "Savage:
The Dory Sief Story,"

08:57.458 --> 08:59.625
directed by the genius
Lassie Kazar,

08:59.708 --> 09:02.541
who won a Ladypants Award
for "Einstein in Miami."

09:02.625 --> 09:05.291
Oh, my God, right?
But yeah.

09:05.375 --> 09:08.041
So you can regard this post as
the official cast announcement

09:08.125 --> 09:09.791
of me playing Dory Sief.

09:09.875 --> 09:11.125
[laughs]

09:11.208 --> 09:12.750
And just to share
a little bit with you guys,

09:12.833 --> 09:14.291
shooting has been
going so well

09:14.375 --> 09:16.250
and it's just been
so incredible to, like,

09:16.333 --> 09:18.375
relive my life.

09:18.458 --> 09:20.000
And yeah,
we're all basically a family.

09:20.083 --> 09:22.958
And you guys are just
always the best,

09:23.041 --> 09:25.875
and it's such an honor being
on this journey with you, so...

09:25.958 --> 09:28.000
[smooches]
Porshe, over and out.

09:28.083 --> 09:30.625
[chuckles]

09:30.708 --> 09:31.958
That was good.

09:32.041 --> 09:33.916
That felt, actually,
really, really good.

09:34.000 --> 09:35.333
I'm really glad
that I did that.

09:35.416 --> 09:37.625
- Mm-hmm.
And they wanted you to do that?

09:37.708 --> 09:38.791
- Uh-huh.
- Uh-huh.

09:38.875 --> 09:41.458
- Mm-hmm.
[cell phone buzzing]

09:41.541 --> 09:42.875
The director's calling me.

09:42.958 --> 09:45.083
Shit, shit, shit.
God.

09:45.166 --> 09:46.958
- You weren't supposed to
do that, were you?

09:47.041 --> 09:48.666
- No.
- Oh, God, sweetie--

09:48.750 --> 09:50.166
- But Elliott,
I heard this rumor

09:50.250 --> 09:51.833
they were gonna recast
me with Selena Gomez.

09:51.916 --> 09:53.333
- Excuse me?
- Yeah, and so,

09:53.416 --> 09:55.166
I was, like, freaking out,
and I just thought

09:55.250 --> 09:57.791
I gotta get ahead of this,
and if I do something about it,

09:57.875 --> 09:59.875
then I'll be, like, reclaiming
my destiny or something,

09:59.958 --> 10:01.458
and now that I did it,
I just feel like

10:01.541 --> 10:03.500
that was a really bad idea.

10:03.583 --> 10:07.083
Shit, shit, shit.
Do I delete it?

10:07.166 --> 10:08.708
- No, no, no, no, no.
Do not delete it.

10:08.791 --> 10:10.958
Do not let them control you.
Just turn your phone off.

10:11.041 --> 10:12.458
Turn it off.
- Okay.

10:12.541 --> 10:14.000
- Yeah.
- Okay, let's go.

10:14.083 --> 10:15.375
- Okay. Good?
- Yup.

10:15.458 --> 10:16.666
- Great.

10:16.750 --> 10:19.083
- I don't believe it.
<i>- What happened?</i>

10:19.166 --> 10:22.583
- No, not you, Richard.
Someone slashed my tires.

10:22.666 --> 10:23.875
[scoffs]

10:23.958 --> 10:27.541
Clearly, they're jealous of
unapologetic wealth.

10:27.625 --> 10:29.916
- Hey, I can get that fixed
for you if you want.

10:30.000 --> 10:31.916
Might take me about
half hour or so.

10:32.000 --> 10:33.375
- All right.
Fine, fine, fine, fine.

10:33.458 --> 10:36.458
Just take it out of the $2,000.

10:36.541 --> 10:38.583
Okay, now what am I gonna do
for half an hour?

10:38.666 --> 10:41.666
- Well, there's a sex museum
right over there.

10:41.750 --> 10:43.333
[faint pop music playing]

10:43.416 --> 10:45.041
- Babe, can you please
take the wig off?

10:45.125 --> 10:46.458
It's making me uncomfortable.

10:46.541 --> 10:48.041
- Elliott, I can't take
the wig off, okay?

10:48.125 --> 10:49.541
I just tried, and it's glued
and it, like,

10:49.625 --> 10:51.375
ripped my extensions out.
- Okay, okay.

10:51.458 --> 10:53.541
- Also the director just texted
me that it's worth $40,000,

10:53.625 --> 10:55.291
and if I mess it up, they're
taking it out of my pay.

10:55.375 --> 10:56.833
So don't make me
feel worse about it.

10:56.916 --> 10:58.083
- Turn your phone off.

10:58.166 --> 10:59.500
- I don't wanna
turn my phone off,

10:59.583 --> 11:01.083
because people are
congratulating me.

11:01.166 --> 11:02.625
- Hi.

11:02.708 --> 11:05.458
So this is a picture
of our friend,

11:05.541 --> 11:08.875
and we just had a few questions
about where they are now.

11:08.958 --> 11:11.583
This picture was
taken here on Thursday,

11:11.666 --> 11:13.291
so we were just wondering
if was possible

11:13.375 --> 11:17.166
to speak to someone who was
maybe working on Thursday.

11:17.250 --> 11:20.041
- Are you guys
friends with Jay-Z?

11:20.125 --> 11:21.250
- I'm sorry?

11:21.333 --> 11:23.833
- I saw your
New York license plates.

11:23.916 --> 11:25.666
Do you guys know Jay-Z?

11:25.750 --> 11:28.458
- No, we don't, but if you
could please just tell us

11:28.541 --> 11:30.750
who was working here on
Thursday, that would be great.

11:30.833 --> 11:33.208
- Yeah, that was me.
I saw that girl.

11:33.291 --> 11:34.916
- Oh, cool!

11:35.000 --> 11:36.333
Did she seem like, you know,

11:36.416 --> 11:37.958
she might be in trouble or
anything?

11:38.041 --> 11:39.708
Like, was she alone or...

11:39.791 --> 11:42.666
- She was with some lady with,
like, an old vibe.

11:42.750 --> 11:45.458
Like, she had red hair
with a white streak in it.

11:45.541 --> 11:46.791
And she said they were friends.

11:46.875 --> 11:49.083
She said it, like,
a million times.

11:49.166 --> 11:51.041
- That's so weird.
- Yeah, who...

11:51.125 --> 11:53.458
- Why would Dory be, like,
friends with an older woman?

11:53.541 --> 11:55.500
- Are you guys scared
of a terrorist attack,

11:55.583 --> 11:57.625
or is that over now?

11:57.708 --> 11:59.916
- Seriously, Richard,
I do not know what possessed me

12:00.000 --> 12:03.791
to buy property in this
surf-and-turf town.

12:03.875 --> 12:06.375
<i>- [indistinct]</i>
- Oh, a penny!

12:06.458 --> 12:08.125
Oh, what a shame
to let that go.

12:08.208 --> 12:09.750
- Portia, why would you
give her your number?

12:09.833 --> 12:11.500
Now she's gonna try to
move in with you.

12:11.583 --> 12:13.875
- 'Cause I remember what it was
like to be her age once.

12:13.958 --> 12:16.583
- You remember how this goes?
Huh?

12:16.666 --> 12:19.541
"Find a penny, pick it up"...
<i>- Pick it up...</i>

12:19.625 --> 12:22.125
- "Kiss your brother
till he's all grown up."

12:22.208 --> 12:24.708
<i>- [laughs]</i>

12:24.791 --> 12:27.041
- Hmm.

12:27.125 --> 12:28.416
Hi, there.

12:28.500 --> 12:30.291
- You're back.

12:30.375 --> 12:32.666
I thought you hated it in here.

12:33.625 --> 12:35.333
- Well, I've never
been in here in my life.

12:35.416 --> 12:38.583
- You were here with
your friend on Thursday.

12:38.666 --> 12:39.875
You were pouty.

12:39.958 --> 12:41.041
- All right, look.

12:41.125 --> 12:42.666
I don't know
what you're talking about,

12:42.750 --> 12:44.458
but I'm choosing
to be offended.

12:44.541 --> 12:46.958
Now this young woman
is who I'm looking for.

12:47.041 --> 12:48.541
Maybe you've seen her
around town?

12:48.625 --> 12:52.416
She might have been with a
charming young man named Chip.

12:52.500 --> 12:53.500
Hmm?

12:53.583 --> 12:55.416
She has a mop of brown,
curly hair.

12:55.500 --> 12:57.583
And we're very worried
about both of them.

12:57.666 --> 13:00.916
- Wait, you're here
looking for her?

13:01.000 --> 13:03.333
She was just in here
looking for you.

13:03.416 --> 13:06.208
- What?
When? Where?

13:06.291 --> 13:07.625
- Like,
two New York minutes ago.

13:07.708 --> 13:11.041
- Where?
- Over there. Right there.

13:11.125 --> 13:12.583
[faint pop music playing]

13:12.666 --> 13:14.458
- You guys, can we go back
and get ice cream?

13:14.541 --> 13:16.041
- [gasps]
Richard, it's the Dory girl.

13:16.125 --> 13:17.875
Oh, my God, she's here.
Shit, I need my car.

13:17.958 --> 13:20.166
<i>- Go get her!</i>

13:20.250 --> 13:22.166
- Do you guys think maybe we
should just go to the police

13:22.250 --> 13:25.375
and ask them if they know
who the older redhead lady is?

13:25.458 --> 13:27.250
- Yeah, and if they don't
know anything,

13:27.333 --> 13:28.833
we can just drive around
town all day.

13:28.916 --> 13:30.000
It's so small.

13:30.083 --> 13:31.291
I mean, it took us two seconds

13:31.375 --> 13:32.833
to drive around
the whole big toe.

13:32.916 --> 13:34.416
- Shut up, shut up!
Red hair, white streak!

13:34.500 --> 13:35.958
Red hair, white streak!
- Drew, follow her!

13:36.041 --> 13:37.458
Go, go, go!
- Okay, okay, okay.

13:37.541 --> 13:39.250
- The Dory girl
is with a group of people.

13:39.333 --> 13:41.875
If I follow her,
she may lead us to Chip.

13:41.958 --> 13:44.291
I'm not running, because
I don't wanna look suspicious.

13:44.375 --> 13:46.250
And also, my doctor told me
to stop running

13:46.333 --> 13:47.500
when I'm wearing heels.

13:47.583 --> 13:49.625
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

13:49.708 --> 13:51.250
- Careful, Drew.
Don't spook her.

13:51.333 --> 13:53.083
- I'm stalking a woman.
I'm going one mile per hour.

13:53.166 --> 13:54.541
Of course it's gonna
look spooky.

13:54.625 --> 13:56.250
- Just drive normal.
- If I drive normal,

13:56.333 --> 13:57.750
I'm gonna pass her!

13:57.833 --> 13:59.250
- God, Drew!
Well, then do something else

13:59.333 --> 14:01.916
so it just, like,
makes it seem normal.

14:02.000 --> 14:04.625
- What else could I be doing?
I'm driving the car.

14:04.708 --> 14:06.291
- Just pretend like you're
brushing your teeth.

14:06.375 --> 14:07.958
Do we have a toothbrush?
- Brush your teeth!

14:08.041 --> 14:09.583
- Why would I be
brushing my teeth?

14:09.666 --> 14:11.750
- Brush your teeth!
- I'm not--

14:11.833 --> 14:13.541
- Hurry, hurry, hurry.
All right.

14:13.625 --> 14:15.750
Stop, stop, stop, stop, stop,
stop, stop, cease, cease.

14:15.833 --> 14:17.916
No, don't put in any more.
Don't--close it!

14:18.000 --> 14:19.541
I've gotta go.
I'll come back for the rest.

14:19.625 --> 14:21.125
- Okay.
- Oh.

14:21.208 --> 14:23.625
- Just act normal.
Just be cool.

14:23.708 --> 14:29.458
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:30.666 --> 14:32.458
- They just pulled in
to get gas.

14:32.541 --> 14:34.958
I am in the perfect position
to follow them.

14:35.041 --> 14:36.500
<i>- Oh, boy.</i>

14:36.583 --> 14:38.708
- When they pull out,
I'll be right on their tail.

14:38.791 --> 14:40.291
- Why won't she pull out?

14:40.375 --> 14:42.750
- My God, when's she gonna go?

14:42.833 --> 14:45.000
- [huffs]

14:45.083 --> 14:47.291
- What is she doing?

14:47.375 --> 14:49.458
- All right, I'm just gonna
pull up and wait for her there.

14:49.541 --> 14:50.500
- That's smart.

14:50.583 --> 14:52.666
- Yeah--ooh.

14:54.708 --> 14:57.416
- Let the chase begin!

14:59.833 --> 15:01.666
- Oh, so now she's pulling out?

15:01.750 --> 15:04.291
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:04.375 --> 15:06.208
[tires squeal]

15:07.541 --> 15:09.916
<i>- Look, look, look!</i>
<i>A roundabout! That's perfect.</i>

15:10.000 --> 15:13.083
<i>We'll loop around</i>
<i>and take her exit.</i>

15:20.083 --> 15:23.458
Okay, here we go.

15:27.750 --> 15:30.291
- What the hell is happening?
Why won't she pick an exit?

15:30.375 --> 15:31.500
- I don't know.

15:31.583 --> 15:33.458
- Well, maybe she's lost
or confused.

15:33.541 --> 15:34.833
- Richard,
you won't believe this.

15:34.916 --> 15:37.208
They're going around
in circles.

15:37.291 --> 15:40.166
They must be lost or confused.

15:40.250 --> 15:43.458
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:43.541 --> 15:44.708
- No!

15:44.791 --> 15:46.916
Pick an exit!
- What is wrong with her?

15:47.000 --> 15:49.125
Does she have, like, dementia?

15:49.208 --> 15:51.375
- Portia, careful.
- What? Is that offensive?

15:51.458 --> 15:53.416
- Yeah.
- Just pick an exit!

15:53.500 --> 15:54.708
- Pick an exit!

15:54.791 --> 15:56.333
- What are they doing?

15:56.416 --> 15:58.166
These kids, they don't know
how to drive.

15:58.250 --> 15:59.666
They don't know how to exit.

15:59.750 --> 16:00.708
both: Go!

16:00.791 --> 16:02.041
- Go!
- Take that one!

16:02.125 --> 16:03.291
- Oh, my God!

16:03.375 --> 16:04.833
- Or that one!
- Just--I don't like--

16:04.916 --> 16:06.875
- Pick a hole, any hole!
Go through the hole!

16:06.958 --> 16:08.291
- I'm starting to get upset!

16:08.375 --> 16:10.208
- Ah.

16:10.291 --> 16:11.916
Come on.
Oh, oh.

16:12.000 --> 16:14.708
Oh, they're up to something.

16:14.791 --> 16:16.875
- [sighs]
- This is so weird.

16:16.958 --> 16:18.375
What is happening?

16:18.458 --> 16:21.166
- They think they're gonna
lose me, they're crazy.

16:21.250 --> 16:23.166
I'm on 'em.
I'm on 'em.

16:23.250 --> 16:26.208
- I think she's chasing us now.
- Oh, God, she is cha--

16:26.291 --> 16:28.083
she's actually getting fast--
- Is she chasing me?

16:28.166 --> 16:29.541
- Oh, God.
- Oh, okay.

16:29.625 --> 16:31.833
Yeah, you wanna chase me?
- Shit, no, no, no.

16:31.916 --> 16:34.375
God, this is fast.
Oh, God!

16:34.458 --> 16:36.708
- Things are heating up now,
Richard.

16:36.791 --> 16:39.458
I'm on this.
I got it.

16:39.541 --> 16:41.583
[tires squealing]

16:41.666 --> 16:48.875
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:51.041 --> 16:53.166
- What in the world
is going on?

16:53.250 --> 16:55.500
- It's two cars.

16:55.583 --> 16:58.791
They seem to be having
some kind of trouble exiting.

17:01.166 --> 17:05.416
- Get off our ass.
- Yeah, and stop, lady!

17:05.500 --> 17:07.500
Ugh, I hate people!

17:07.583 --> 17:09.333
- Wait, wait.
- What?

17:09.416 --> 17:11.791
It's Dory!
both: What?

17:11.875 --> 17:14.583
- Oh, my God!
- Oh, my God, oh, my God!

17:14.666 --> 17:16.375
[metal crunches, all grunt]

17:16.458 --> 17:19.208
- That wasn't my fault.
That was not my fault.

17:19.291 --> 17:21.166
- Oh, my God!
- What the hell was that?

17:21.250 --> 17:23.666
- Oh, God.
Oh, God.

17:23.750 --> 17:26.291
- The twink!

17:26.375 --> 17:27.541
- No.

17:27.625 --> 17:29.625
- Oh, shit.

17:29.708 --> 17:32.583
- No, no, no, not them.
- It's okay.

17:32.666 --> 17:35.375
- Not them, not them, no!
- Wait, Stephanie.

17:35.458 --> 17:36.958
Stephanie, wait!

17:37.041 --> 17:39.625
I'm stuck, Stephanie!
Wait!

17:39.708 --> 17:41.875
- Dory, wait, it's okay!
It's us!

17:41.958 --> 17:43.500
- She's running away!
What do we do?

17:43.583 --> 17:45.500
- Oh, I don't know!
Just run after her!

17:45.583 --> 17:47.375
- [screams]
- Well, I just--

17:47.458 --> 17:50.416
fucking find us, Drew!
I don't know!

17:50.500 --> 17:52.541
- [screams]

17:52.625 --> 17:55.125
[tires squeal]

17:55.208 --> 17:56.541
- [grunts]

17:56.625 --> 17:58.708
- What is she doing...
[indistinct]

17:58.791 --> 18:01.958
[both panting]

18:03.166 --> 18:05.500
- I won't let you
ruin my life again!

18:05.583 --> 18:09.000
- What are you talking about?
We're your friends!

18:09.083 --> 18:11.500
- Dory, stop running!

18:11.583 --> 18:13.041
<i>[tense music]</i>

18:13.125 --> 18:15.291
We're trying to save you, babe!

18:15.375 --> 18:16.750
- Stephanie, wait!

18:16.833 --> 18:18.916
- Young man, what are you doing
in my Chanel?

18:19.000 --> 18:20.500
Richard, I'm putting you
on hold.

18:20.583 --> 18:22.416
- No!
Wait, Stephanie!

18:22.500 --> 18:25.125
I'm stuck!
[grunts]

18:25.208 --> 18:26.500
- You stop screaming.

18:26.583 --> 18:28.333
Stop screaming,
and you'll get out.

18:28.416 --> 18:29.875
- Stephanie!
- Take a breath.

18:29.958 --> 18:32.666
- [yells] I'm stuck!
It's stuck! It's stuck!

18:32.750 --> 18:34.041
- Such a lemon, this car,

18:34.125 --> 18:35.541
just like everything else
in this town.

18:35.625 --> 18:37.250
I don't even know how I got
in possession of this.

18:37.333 --> 18:39.333
It was probably a gift
from one of my lovers,

18:39.416 --> 18:40.500
one of my many lovers.

18:40.583 --> 18:41.750
- Stephanie!

18:41.833 --> 18:44.500
- Dory!
You should be thrilled!

18:44.583 --> 18:45.916
- [screams]

18:46.000 --> 18:47.875
- What the--
- No!

18:47.958 --> 18:49.500
[panting]

18:49.583 --> 18:51.416
Oh, no!
Oh, shit!

18:51.500 --> 18:52.875
[yells]
Let me go!

18:52.958 --> 18:55.708
- Drew, Drew, pop the trunk!
- Let me go!

18:55.791 --> 18:57.416
[both screaming]

18:57.500 --> 18:59.875
- Drew,
she is feral and in a wig!

18:59.958 --> 19:03.041
Come on, Portia, help her!
- I'm trying!

19:03.125 --> 19:06.416
- No, no, no, no!
- Ow!

19:06.500 --> 19:08.125
Not in the car!
Not in the car!

19:08.208 --> 19:09.833
Ow!
- Shit!

19:09.916 --> 19:12.833
[all yelling at once]

19:12.916 --> 19:14.750
- Dory--
- Shit! No! No!

19:14.833 --> 19:16.416
- Oh, my God. Okay.
- No!

19:16.500 --> 19:18.083
- Let me go!
- Stop! Stop!

19:18.166 --> 19:20.083
- Let's go, go, go, go.
- Is she gonna die in there?

19:20.166 --> 19:21.875
- I don't know.
- Can she breathe?

19:21.958 --> 19:23.083
Oh, shit.

19:23.166 --> 19:25.083
We love you, Dory!

19:25.166 --> 19:28.458
- Okay.
Okay. Let's go.

19:28.541 --> 19:34.291
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:34.375 --> 19:36.250
- Sweetheart,
I know what we're gonna do.

19:36.333 --> 19:37.750
Just calm down, don't move,

19:37.833 --> 19:39.750
and I'm gonna
cut you out of it.

19:39.833 --> 19:41.250
I'm sure that I have

19:41.333 --> 19:43.541
my cocktail scissors
in here somewhere.

19:43.625 --> 19:44.708
- No!

19:44.791 --> 19:47.416
It's too late!
We're too late!

19:47.500 --> 19:48.916
Oh!

19:49.000 --> 19:51.583
I hate you,
you evil witch!

19:51.666 --> 19:54.375
- Don't you talk
to your mother like that.

19:57.833 --> 19:59.791
- [exhales softly]

19:59.875 --> 20:01.583
M...

20:01.666 --> 20:03.208
my mother?

20:04.250 --> 20:06.916
- Did I say that?

20:07.000 --> 20:09.750
Well, I--this was
never supposed to happen.

20:09.833 --> 20:12.083
- You're...

20:12.166 --> 20:14.291
you're my Aunt Lylah.

20:14.375 --> 20:16.000
- I am.

20:16.083 --> 20:18.208
And I'm also your mother.

20:18.291 --> 20:22.166
Your mummy.
I'm your auntie and your mummy.

20:22.250 --> 20:24.250
And that can be a good thing,
because, you know,

20:24.333 --> 20:26.291
it's not everyone
that gets to be both things,

20:26.375 --> 20:28.500
and I can be both things
to a child.

20:28.583 --> 20:30.416
- No, no, no, no, no!

20:30.500 --> 20:34.291
I knew there was something
you all were hiding from me!

20:34.375 --> 20:37.250
All those whispers!
Oh, my God!

20:37.333 --> 20:40.291
This is why no one wants to be
my friend!

20:40.375 --> 20:43.791
Because I'm a freak!
I'm a little freak!!

20:43.875 --> 20:46.166
[crying]

20:46.250 --> 20:48.583
- Richard, he knows.
<i>- Christ.</i>

20:48.666 --> 20:50.791
- [screaming]

20:50.875 --> 20:53.500
- Stop, Dory!
Please, stop screaming.

20:53.583 --> 20:54.666
Please, I'm begging you!

20:54.750 --> 20:56.333
I'm begging you!
It's getting so old!

20:56.416 --> 20:57.833
- Okay. Dory. Dory.

20:57.916 --> 20:59.791
Dory, if you stop screaming,
we'll take the tape off.

20:59.875 --> 21:01.000
- Yes.
- If you stop screaming,

21:01.083 --> 21:02.333
we'll take the tape off.

21:02.416 --> 21:03.708
- Good idea. Yes.
- Okay, I'm going in.

21:03.791 --> 21:05.291
Thank you.
Thank you for stopping.

21:05.375 --> 21:07.083
- Good girl, good girl.
- Thank you for stopping.

21:07.166 --> 21:08.833
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.
- Yay, good job.

21:08.916 --> 21:10.958
- Okay, wow.
- Help!

21:11.041 --> 21:12.166
Chip!

21:12.250 --> 21:13.458
Help!

21:13.541 --> 21:16.166
Chip!
- Dory! Dory, stop!

21:16.250 --> 21:18.166
Look at my eyes, Dory.
It's me.

21:18.250 --> 21:20.083
It's us.
We're your friends.

21:20.166 --> 21:22.750
- You're not my friends!

21:22.833 --> 21:24.666
And you never have been.

21:24.750 --> 21:28.208
Ugh!
You ruined my life!

21:28.291 --> 21:33.458
And my name is Stephanie!
It's not Dory!

21:33.541 --> 21:36.333
I hate you all so much!

21:36.416 --> 21:38.958
You don't want
what's best for me.

21:39.041 --> 21:41.750
You're just a bunch of
self-obsessed,

21:41.833 --> 21:45.041
narcissistic sociopaths!

21:45.125 --> 21:46.958
- [laughs] Okay, fascinating,

21:47.041 --> 21:48.750
coming from you, of all people.

21:48.833 --> 21:51.541
- [screaming]
- Dory!

21:51.625 --> 21:53.333
Wake up, okay?

21:53.416 --> 21:54.708
Wake up, Dory!
It's me!

21:54.791 --> 21:57.250
I'm Portia!
I'm your best friend!

21:57.333 --> 22:00.875
I am a good friend
and you are a bad friend, okay?

22:00.958 --> 22:02.208
- Yeah, we came here
to save you!

22:02.291 --> 22:04.375
- Yes!
- You stubborn idiot!

22:04.458 --> 22:06.625
Every time we try to help you,
our lives get worse!

22:06.708 --> 22:08.958
We would be happy
if it wasn't for you!

22:09.041 --> 22:11.291
- And you know what else?
You know what else?

22:11.375 --> 22:13.833
Uh, Stephanie is a bad name!

22:13.916 --> 22:16.791
- It's a stupid name, Dory!

22:16.875 --> 22:18.541
[pants]

22:18.625 --> 22:21.625
- [growling]

22:21.708 --> 22:24.875
[grunting]

22:28.083 --> 22:29.625
- I mean, did you see her eyes?

22:29.708 --> 22:32.791
There was nothing, nothing.
It was just rage.

22:32.875 --> 22:34.875
I think she's gone.

22:34.958 --> 22:36.416
- What do we do?

22:36.500 --> 22:38.708
She's been brainwashed
or something.

22:38.791 --> 22:40.458
We're not equipped
to handle this.

22:40.541 --> 22:42.583
- You guys,
we can't give up, okay?

22:42.666 --> 22:43.791
Seriously.

22:43.875 --> 22:45.791
If we give up,
she could kill us,

22:45.875 --> 22:48.833
and we know
what she's capable of.

22:51.583 --> 22:53.500
- Let me try something.

22:53.583 --> 22:56.750
- [shouting]

23:00.166 --> 23:03.291
[panting]

23:15.125 --> 23:17.208
- Hey.

23:17.291 --> 23:20.958
I'm gonna take the tape off.

23:21.041 --> 23:22.875
Okay?

23:27.250 --> 23:29.958
- [gasps, pants]

23:30.041 --> 23:33.416
- Just me and you.

23:33.500 --> 23:35.583
Just Dory and Drew.

23:41.041 --> 23:43.166
[sighs]

23:43.250 --> 23:47.208
We have been through
a lot together.

23:49.708 --> 23:53.166
I feel like you know me
better than anyone else.

23:56.166 --> 23:58.333
And I kinda feel like
I'm the only person

23:58.416 --> 24:00.791
who really knows who you are.

24:05.125 --> 24:08.541
I guess what
I'm trying to say is that...

24:11.041 --> 24:14.375
I think that
you're still in there.

24:14.458 --> 24:17.208
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

24:17.291 --> 24:22.375
The girl that I fell in love
with is still in there.

24:22.458 --> 24:25.208
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:25.291 --> 24:28.500
I can see her so clearly.

24:30.583 --> 24:33.041
I know she didn't slip away.

24:36.458 --> 24:40.083
Please come back, Dory.

24:40.166 --> 24:42.291
Please come back.

24:42.375 --> 24:45.625
- [spits]

24:45.708 --> 24:47.875
I'll kill you.

24:47.958 --> 24:49.750
I'll kill all of you.

24:49.833 --> 24:52.416
Chip is gonna save me,
and then we'll both kill you

24:52.500 --> 24:54.291
for what you've done to us!

24:54.375 --> 24:57.791
Chip, help!
Help!

24:57.875 --> 24:59.125
- Nope, nope, nope, nope.

24:59.208 --> 25:00.708
I refuse to keep listening

25:00.791 --> 25:02.875
to her moaning and screaming

25:02.958 --> 25:04.750
like she's giving birth
to a devil baby.

25:04.833 --> 25:07.083
I'm turning up this TV,
I will not listen to this.

25:07.166 --> 25:09.250
La-la-la-la-la
la-la-la-la-la.

25:09.333 --> 25:10.875
<i>- Overnight,</i>
<i>flurries will increase</i>

25:10.958 --> 25:13.250
<i>with a total accumulations</i>
<i>of three inches.</i>

25:13.333 --> 25:15.583
- [yelling]

25:15.666 --> 25:17.166
<i>- ...with a high of 34.</i>

25:17.250 --> 25:19.625
<i>It's currently 48 degrees.</i>

25:19.708 --> 25:21.750
<i>[dynamic music playing]</i>

25:21.833 --> 25:25.166
<i>- Are these the last days</i>
<i>of Charlie Reeny's life?</i>

25:25.250 --> 25:27.166
<i>Find out on our</i>
<i>live 24-hour feed</i>

25:27.250 --> 25:29.083
<i>into her hospital room</i>
<i>that will document</i>

25:29.166 --> 25:32.625
<i>every upsetting second</i>
